The paper discusses the development of artificial oscillator-based spiking neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also explores the synchronization of oscillators, which is related to the field of electronics and electrical engineering (cs.ET) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the classification and computing capabilities of the oscillator-based spiking neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT).
